column1: Table 18. Supplemental data for state governments
Report title: Justice Expenditure and Employment Extracts 2013 Final, NCJ 250327
Data source: Justice Expenditure and Employment Extracts Program (JEEE)
Author: Jennifer Bronson, Ph.D., BJS Statistician
Table 18.  Supplemental data for state governments
Note: Local government data are estimates subject to variability.

Population figures are from the Bureau of the Census, Table 1. Annual Estimates of the Resident Population for the United States, regions, states, and Puerto Rico: April 1, 2010 to July 1, 2016 (NST-EST2016-01), December 2016.
a/"Personal income" is from the U.S. Department of Commerce, Survey of Current Business, August 2013.
b/"Total general expenditure" excludes utilities, state-operated liquor stores, and insurance trust benefits.
c/"General functions only" FTE excludes utilities, and state-operated liquor stores.
